  <mads:note type="source">"Macer, Bae'bius, One of the consuls suffecti A.D. 101, was consul
      designatus when the younger Pliny pleaded the cause of Bassus before the senate." Smith's
      Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 2, 1870, p. 883.</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">"Baebius Macer, cos. suff. in AD 103, consular governor of Dacia in 113
      (unpublished military diploma), praef. urbi in 117. Although the praef. praetorio Attianus
      found him suspicious, he was not executed by Hadrian (SHA Hadr. 5,5; Fost2, 46, 98)."
      "Baebius." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider
      . Brill, 2007. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 27 July 2007</mads:note>
